2️⃣ What Is Spring Boot (Conceptually)

Spring Boot is:

A framework to build production-ready applications fast

Opinionated → sensible defaults

Removes boilerplate configuration

What Spring Boot Handles for Us

Server setup (Tomcat)

Dependency management

Auto-configuration

Application startup lifecycle

3️⃣ Why Maven Is Used
Maven Solves:

Dependency management

Build lifecycle

Version consistency

Important Files
pom.xml  → dependencies + plugins


Key idea:

Maven ensures everyone builds the app the same way.

4️⃣ Project Structure (VERY IMPORTANT)
com.bank
 ├── BankingApplication.java
 ├── controller
 ├── service
 ├── repository
 ├── model
 └── config

Why This Structure?
Layer	Responsibility
controller	Handles HTTP requests
service	Business logic
repository	DB access
model	Entities / DTOs
config	Security, configs

👉 Separation of concerns
👉 Easy to split into microservices later

5️⃣ Entry Point: BankingApplication.java
@SpringBootApplication
public class BankingApplication {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        SpringApplication.run(BankingApplication.class, args);
    }
}

What @SpringBootApplication Does

It combines:

@Configuration

@EnableAutoConfiguration

@ComponentScan

👉 Spring scans and wires everything automatically.

6️⃣ What Is a REST Controller
Purpose

Exposes APIs to the outside world

Converts HTTP → Java method

Example:

@RestController
@RequestMapping("/health")
public class HealthController {

    @GetMapping
    public String health() {
        return "Banking system is up";
    }
}

Key Annotations

@RestController → REST API

@RequestMapping → base path

@GetMapping → HTTP GET

7️⃣ Request Flow (Mental Model)
Client
 → HTTP Request
 → Controller
 → Service
 → (Repository)
 → Response


For Day 2:

